# Trivy ignore file — reviewed, time-boxed suppressions.
#
# Trivy (fs scan, HIGH/CRITICAL, exit-code 1) runs in CI security-scan
# (.github/workflows/ci.yml). It auto-reads this file from the repo root.
#
# --- brace-expansion ReDoS, bundled inside aws-cdk-lib -----------------------
# CVE-2026-13149 (HIGH): brace-expansion denial-of-service via exponential-time
# complexity. Present as aws-cdk-lib > minimatch > brace-expansion@5.0.5 in
# infra/package-lock.json.
#
# Why suppressed (not fixable by us):
#   - brace-expansion is `"inBundle": true` inside aws-cdk-lib's vendored tree,
#     so an npm `overrides` entry does NOT reach it (see the "comment:overrides"
#     note in infra/package.json). It clears only when aws-cdk-lib ships a
#     rebuilt bundle with a patched brace-expansion (>= 5.0.7 / 2.1.2 / 1.1.16).
#   - Verified 2026-07-21: the latest aws-cdk-lib (2.261.0) still bundles 5.0.6,
#     which is below the 5.0.7 fix — upgrading aws-cdk-lib does not resolve it.
#   - Impact is CDK build/synth-time only (glob over our own repo files, not
#     untrusted input); aws-cdk-lib never enters the production container.
#
# Re-review when aws-cdk-lib publishes a bundle with brace-expansion >= 5.0.7;
# drop this line and let the scan pass on its own. Revisit by 2026-10-21.
CVE-2026-13149
